  <title translate="true">CountsperCycle</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">X-Axis:<keyword translate="true">Counts per Cycle</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para><table styleclass="MotionPupup" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Parameter" translate="true">Counts per Cycle</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">: If you are designing motions for a servo system or stepper motor system, then you may have a Pacer (sometimes known as a Master) Encoder that &apos;sets the drum beat&apos; for the other axes to synchronise their motions with.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Parameter" translate="true">Counts per Cycle</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> allows you to give the number of counts in a complete turn or the complete range of movement of the Master or Pacer Encoder. The value you will need to enter will be dependent on your control system and the pacer encoder resolution.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">If the motion settings units of the X–axis are set to counts, then the Pacer motion (X–axis) can be output at equal increments in the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Tools-DataTransfer" styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">Data-Transfer Tool</link><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">If you want to save the data as integer, then set the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Decimal-Places" styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">Dec.Places</link><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> value to zero in the Data Format form.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
